    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''New Generation of Qaeda Chiefs Is Seen on Rise'' (front page, April 2):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''New Generation of Qaeda Chiefs Is Seen on Rise'' (front page, April 2):</p>
        <p>The idea that our intelligence officials are surprised and dismayed by Al Qaeda's ability to raise up new leaders is both surprising and horrifying. Are they, like the Bush administration, so blinded by the belief in American might and superiority that they simply assumed that anything we did would bring ''victory''?</p>
        <p>It is plain to the rest of us that the forces of terror have an endless supply of willing fighters. It would be surprising if they did not have substantive leadership potential among those thousands of men.</p>
        <p>We will never be safe in this country until the intelligence community changes how it thinks and operates.</p>
        <p>Anne-Marie Hislop  Davenport, Iowa, April 2, 2007</p>
      </block>
